org.usb4java

Interface TransferCallback


  • public interface TransferCallback
    Asynchronous transfer callback. When submitting asynchronous transfers, you pass a callback of this type via the callback member of the Transfer structure.
    Author:
    Luca Longinotti (l@longi.li)

    • Method Detail

      • processTransfer

        void processTransfer(Transfer transfer)
        Processes a transfer notification. libusb will call this function later, when the transfer has completed or failed.
        Parameters:
        transfer - The Transfer the callback is being notified about.
